rough the settings panel. \r\n\r\n<h2>Solution</h2>\r\n\r\n[php title=\"Before: Notice the &#039;wordpress&#039; username.\"]the_widget(\'TwitterWidget\', array(\'title\'=&gt;__(\'My latest tweets\',\'mystique\'), \'twituser\'=&gt;\'wordpress\', \'twitcount\'=&gt;\'5\'), array(\'widget_id\'=&gt;\'instance-twitterwidget\',\'before_widget\' =&gt; \'&lt;li class=&quot;block&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-twitter&quot;&gt;\',\'after_widget\' =&gt; \'&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\',\'before_title\' =&gt; \'&lt;h3 class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;\',\'after_title\' =&gt; \'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-div&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-div-arrow&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\'));[/php]\r\n\r\n[php title=\"After: Changing the hardcoded username fixed it right up!\"]the_widget(\'TwitterWidget\', array(\'title\'=&gt;__(\'My latest tweets\',\'mystique\'), \'twituser\'=&gt;\'kiapierce\', \'twitcount\'=&gt;\'5\'), array(\'widget_id\'=&gt;\'instance-twitterwidget\',\'before_widget\' =&gt; \'&lt;li class=&quot;block&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-twitter&quot;&gt;\',\'after_widget\' =&gt; \'&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;\',\'before_title\' =&gt; \'&lt;h3 class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;\',\'after_title\' =&gt; \'&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-div&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;block-div-arrow&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\'));[/php]\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\nThis was such a pain in the ass, and the fix being so easy only made it worse. *sigh* Oh well, you live and you learn :)\r\n\r\nUntil next time.','Fixing the Twitter Plugin in Mystique','','publish','open','open','','fixing-the-twitter-plugin-in-mystique','','','2011-02-12 00:04:04','2011-02-12 06:04:04','',0,'http://nerdtraining.info/?p=28',0,'post','',0),(29,1,'2011-02-12 00:00:25','2011-02-12 06:00:25','Hey guys, just a quick thing. \n\nI am currently using the Wordpress theme \"Mystique\" for the blog, though this will change as soon as I have time to put toget